              "type": "exercise",
              "kind": "recall",
              "mode": "sync",
              "prompt": "Drill the TTL **live-window** check blank-slate. Build a class `TTLCell` whose storage holds, per key, a tuple `(value, created_at, expiry)` where `expiry` is `None` for no-TTL entries.\n\nMethods:\n  - `set_at(key, value, timestamp)` — no TTL; store `(value, timestamp, None)`.\n  - `set_at_with_ttl(key, value, timestamp, ttl)` — store `(value, timestamp, timestamp + ttl)`.\n  - `get_at(key, timestamp)` — return the value only if the cell is **live** at `timestamp`, else `None`.\n\nA cell with a TTL is live exactly when `created_at <= now < expiry` (creation is inclusive, expiry is exclusive). A cell with `expiry is None` is live for any `now >= created_at`. A missing key is never live.\n\nExample: `c = TTLCell(); c.set_at_with_ttl(\"a\", \"1\", 10, 5)` → live window `[10, 15)`: `get_at(\"a\", 10)` and `get_at(\"a\", 14)` return `\"1\"`; `get_at(\"a\", 9)` and `get_at(\"a\", 15)` return `None`.",
              "solution": "class TTLCell:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._db = {}  # key -> (value, created_at, expiry)\n\n    def _live(self, cell, now):\n        if cell is None:\n            return False\n        created_at, expiry = cell[1], cell[2]\n        if expiry is None:\n            return created_at <= now\n        return created_at <= now < expiry\n\n    def set_at(self, key, value, timestamp):\n        self._db[key] = (value, timestamp, None)\n\n    def set_at_with_ttl(self, key, value, timestamp, ttl):\n        self._db[key] = (value, timestamp, timestamp + ttl)\n\n    def get_at(self, key, timestamp):\n        cell = self._db.get(key)\n        if not self._live(cell, timestamp):\n            return None\n        return cell[0]\n",
              "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import TTLCell\n\n\nclass ExerciseTests(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_before_creation_is_dead(self):\n        c = TTLCell()\n        c.set_at_with_ttl(\"a\", \"1\", 10, 5)  # live window [10, 15)\n        self.assertIsNone(c.get_at(\"a\", 9))\n\n    def test_at_creation_is_live(self):\n        c = TTLCell()\n        c.set_at_with_ttl(\"a\", \"1\", 10, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(c.get_at(\"a\", 10), \"1\")  # created_at <= now\n\n    def test_inside_window_is_live(self):\n        c = TTLCell()\n        c.set_at_with_ttl(\"a\", \"1\", 10, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(c.get_at(\"a\", 14), \"1\")\n\n    def test_at_expiry_is_dead(self):\n        c = TTLCell()\n        c.set_at_with_ttl(\"a\", \"1\", 10, 5)\n        self.assertIsNone(c.get_at(\"a\", 15))  # now == expiry -> excluded\n\n    def test_no_ttl_is_permanent_after_creation(self):\n        c = TTLCell()\n        c.set_at(\"a\", \"1\", 10)\n        self.assertEqual(c.get_at(\"a\", 10**9), \"1\")\n        self.assertIsNone(c.get_at(\"a\", 9))  # still dead before creation\n\n    def test_missing_key_is_none(self):\n        self.assertIsNone(TTLCell().get_at(\"nope\", 0))\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
