          "kind": "recall",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "Write a `Threshold` class configured with a cutoff number.\n\n- `__init__(self, cutoff)` stores `self.cutoff`.\n- `__call__(self, x)` returns `True` if `x >= self.cutoff`, else `False`, making each instance behave like a configured predicate function.\n\nExample: `passing = Threshold(60)` then `passing(75)` is `True` and `passing(40)` is `False`; `callable(passing)` is `True`; and `list(map(Threshold(0), [-1, 0, 2]))` is `[False, True, True]` because the instance can be passed anywhere a function is expected.",
          "solution": "class Threshold:\n    def __init__(self, cutoff):\n        self.cutoff = cutoff\n\n    def __call__(self, x):\n        # instance behaves like a configured predicate function\n        return x >= self.cutoff\n\n    def __repr__(self):\n        return f\"Threshold({self.cutoff!r})\"\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import Threshold\n\nclass ExerciseTests(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_callable(self):\n        self.assertTrue(callable(Threshold(60)))\n\n    def test_above_cutoff(self):\n        self.assertTrue(Threshold(60)(75))\n\n    def test_at_cutoff_inclusive(self):\n        self.assertTrue(Threshold(60)(60))\n\n    def test_below_cutoff(self):\n        self.assertFalse(Threshold(60)(40))\n\n    def test_distinct_config(self):\n        low, high = Threshold(0), Threshold(100)\n        self.assertTrue(low(5))\n        self.assertFalse(high(5))\n\n    def test_usable_in_map(self):\n        self.assertEqual(list(map(Threshold(0), [-1, 0, 2])), [False, True, True])\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
