          "prompt": "Use `dataclasses` to write a `Rectangle` dataclass with fields `width: float`, `height: float`, and `area: float = 0.0`.\n\nImplement `__post_init__` (which the dataclass runs automatically after the generated `__init__`) so that, when `area` was left at its default of `0.0`, it is set to `width * height`; if the caller explicitly passed a non-zero `area`, leave it untouched.\n\nExample: `Rectangle(3, 4).area` is `12` (derived), while `Rectangle(3, 4, area=99).area` stays `99` (caller override respected).",
