  "title": "Stdlib Power Tools",
  "blurb": "Four modules that ship with every CPython installation — `heapq`, `bisect`, `itertools`, `functools` — quietly solve a disproportionate slice of interview problems. Knowing *when* to reach for each one is the skill: a heap beats a full sort when you only need the top-k; `bisect` turns an O(n) search into O(log n) in a sorted list; `itertools` expresses combinatorial and lazy-sequence work in one readable line; `functools.lru_cache` memoizes any recursive function with a single decorator. This module teaches the full API surface of all four, drills each tool to muscle memory, and closes with cross-tool capstone problems that look exactly like real interview questions.",
