          "type": "text",
          "value": "## heappushpop and heapreplace\n\nWhen you need to push one item then pop the smallest — in a single O(log n) call:\n\n```python\nh = [1, 3, 5]\nheapq.heapify(h)\nresult = heapq.heappushpop(h, 2)   # push 2, immediately pop min -> returns 1; h = [2, 3, 5]\nresult2 = heapq.heapreplace(h, 10) # pop min FIRST (returns 2), then push 10; h = [3, 5, 10]\n```\n\n`heappushpop` is faster than `heappush` followed by `heappop`. It is the tool for maintaining a **fixed-size top-k heap** as you stream data."
