          "prompt": "Implement two functions:\n\n1. `count_in_range(sorted_list, lo, hi)` — count how many elements `x` satisfy `lo <= x <= hi`. Use `bisect_right` and `bisect_left` to compute this in O(log n) with no loop.\n\n2. `left_vs_right(sorted_list, target)` — return a tuple `(bisect_left_index, bisect_right_index)` for `target`. The difference `right - left` equals the number of occurrences.\n\nExamples:\n- `count_in_range([1,2,2,2,3], 2, 2)` → `3`\n- `left_vs_right([1,3,3,3,5], 3)` → `(1, 4)`",
          "solution": "import bisect\n\ndef count_in_range(sorted_list, lo, hi):\n    # bisect_right(hi) - bisect_left(lo) = count of elements in [lo, hi]\n    right = bisect.bisect_right(sorted_list, hi)\n    left = bisect.bisect_left(sorted_list, lo)\n    return right - left\n\ndef left_vs_right(sorted_list, target):\n    left = bisect.bisect_left(sorted_list, target)\n    right = bisect.bisect_right(sorted_list, target)\n    return left, right\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import count_in_range, left_vs_right\n\nclass TestCountInRange(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], 2, 4), 3)\n\n    def test_inclusive_boundaries(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], 1, 5), 5)\n\n    def test_none_in_range(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([1, 2, 3], 10, 20), 0)\n\n    def test_with_duplicates(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([1, 2, 2, 2, 3], 2, 2), 3)\n\n    def test_single_element_match(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([5], 5, 5), 1)\n\n    def test_empty(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_in_range([], 1, 10), 0)\n\nclass TestLeftVsRight(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_no_duplicates(self):\n        self.assertEqual(left_vs_right([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], 3), (2, 3))\n\n    def test_duplicates(self):\n        self.assertEqual(left_vs_right([1, 3, 3, 3, 5], 3), (1, 4))\n\n    def test_count_via_difference(self):\n        l, r = left_vs_right([2, 2, 2], 2)\n        self.assertEqual(r - l, 3)\n\n    def test_missing(self):\n        l, r = left_vs_right([1, 2, 3, 4], 2)\n        self.assertEqual(l, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(r, 2)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
