  "title": "Two Pointers",
  "blurb": "Two pointers is the pattern you reach for whenever a brute-force double loop feels wasteful. The core insight is simple: instead of checking every pair with nested for-loops (O(n²)), plant one pointer at each end of a sorted array and let them walk toward each other, or keep a slow write-cursor and a fast read-cursor moving in the same direction. You spend one pass instead of n². This module drills both flavors — opposite-ends converging and same-direction chasing — on the exact problems that show up in every onsite: Two Sum II, Valid Palindrome, Container With Most Water, Remove Duplicates, Move Zeroes, and the capstone 3Sum. Master the template once; the variants write themselves.",
