          "value": "## Valid Palindrome (LC125) — skip non-alphanumeric from both ends\n\nPalindrome checking is another perfect converging scenario. We want to compare `s[left]` with `s[right]` and move inward. The twist in LC125: skip punctuation and spaces by burning through non-alphanumeric characters before each comparison.\n\n```python\ndef is_palindrome(s):\n    left, right = 0, len(s) - 1\n    while left < right:\n        while left < right and not s[left].isalnum():\n            left += 1   # burn non-alphanumeric from left\n        while left < right and not s[right].isalnum():\n            right -= 1  # burn non-alphanumeric from right\n        if s[left].lower() != s[right].lower():\n            return False\n        left += 1\n        right -= 1\n    return True\n```\n\nBoth inner `while` loops are guarded by `left < right` — that prevents them from crossing each other and going out of bounds."
