          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "recall",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**LC26 — Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array**\n\nGiven a sorted integer array `nums`, remove duplicates **in-place** so each element appears exactly once. Return `k` — the count of unique elements. The first `k` elements of `nums` must hold the result.\n\nUse the write/read pattern: `slow=1`, `fast` starts at 1. When `nums[fast] != nums[slow-1]`, copy `nums[fast]` to `nums[slow]` and advance `slow`.\n\n`remove_duplicates(nums) -> int`\n\nExamples:\n- `nums=[1,1,2]` → returns `2`, `nums[:2] == [1,2]`\n- `nums=[0,0,1,1,1,2,2,3,3,4]` → returns `5`, `nums[:5] == [0,1,2,3,4]`",
          "solution": "def remove_duplicates(nums):\n    if not nums:\n        return 0\n\n    slow = 1  # position 0 is always unique by itself\n    for fast in range(1, len(nums)):\n        if nums[fast] != nums[slow - 1]:\n            nums[slow] = nums[fast]\n            slow += 1\n\n    return slow\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import remove_duplicates\n\nclass TestRemoveDuplicates(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_lc_example1(self):\n        nums = [1, 1, 2]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 2)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [1, 2])\n\n    def test_lc_example2(self):\n        nums = [0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [0, 1, 2, 3, 4])\n\n    def test_empty(self):\n        nums = []\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 0)\n\n    def test_single(self):\n        nums = [7]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [7])\n\n    def test_all_same(self):\n        nums = [5, 5, 5, 5]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [5])\n\n    def test_no_duplicates(self):\n        nums = [1, 2, 3, 4]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 4)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [1, 2, 3, 4])\n\n    def test_negatives(self):\n        nums = [-3, -3, -1, 0, 0, 2]\n        k = remove_duplicates(nums)\n        self.assertEqual(k, 4)\n        self.assertEqual(nums[:k], [-3, -1, 0, 2])\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
