          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "cumulative",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**LC16 — 3Sum Closest (Cumulative Capstone)**\n\nGiven an integer array `nums` and an integer `target`, find three integers whose sum is closest to `target`. Return that sum. Assume exactly one solution exists.\n\nThis combines every skill from the module:\n- Sort `nums` first.\n- Outer loop over anchor `nums[i]`.\n- Converging two pointers on `nums[i+1..n-1]`.\n- Track `best` as the sum with minimum `|sum - target|`.\n- If `s == target`, return immediately (exact match).\n- If `s < target`, advance `left`; if `s > target`, retreat `right`.\n\nNo deduplication needed (you are minimizing distance, not collecting unique triplets).\n\n`three_sum_closest(nums, target) -> int`\n\nExamples:\n- `three_sum_closest([-1,2,1,-4], 1)` → `2` (triplet `-1,2,1`)\n- `three_sum_closest([0,0,0], 1)` → `0`",
          "solution": "def three_sum_closest(nums, target):\n    nums.sort()\n    n = len(nums)\n    # Initialize best to the sum of the first triplet\n    best = nums[0] + nums[1] + nums[2]\n\n    for i in range(n - 2):\n        left = i + 1\n        right = n - 1\n\n        while left < right:\n            s = nums[i] + nums[left] + nums[right]\n\n            if abs(s - target) < abs(best - target):\n                best = s\n\n            if s == target:\n                return s  # can't get closer than exact\n            elif s < target:\n                left += 1\n            else:\n                right -= 1\n\n    return best\n",
