          "prompt": "**Exercise 3 — Longest substring without repeating characters (LC3)**\n\nWrite `length_of_longest_substring(s)` using the expand/shrink template.\n- Maintain a dict `seen` mapping each character to its most recent index.\n- When `s[right]` is already in the window (`seen[ch] >= left`), jump `left` to `seen[ch] + 1` to evict the duplicate.\n- Return the length of the longest valid window seen.\n- Return 0 for empty input.\n\nLeetCode analog: LC3 (Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters).",
          "solution": "def length_of_longest_substring(s):\n    \"\"\"LC3 — longest substring without repeating characters.\"\"\"\n    seen = {}        # char -> most recent index\n    left = 0\n    best = 0\n    for right, ch in enumerate(s):\n        # If ch is inside the current window, jump left past it\n        if ch in seen and seen[ch] >= left:\n            left = seen[ch] + 1\n        seen[ch] = right\n        best = max(best, right - left + 1)\n    return best\n",
