          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "applied",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "Write `product_except_self(nums)` that returns an array where `output[i]` is the product of every element in `nums` except `nums[i]`.\n\nConstraints: no division; O(n) time; O(1) extra space (output array not counted).\n\nTwo-pass: left products in one forward pass, multiply by right products in a backward pass.\n\nLeetCode analog: **Product of Array Except Self (LC 238)**.",
          "solution": "def product_except_self(nums):\n    \"\"\"Return array where output[i] = product of all elements except nums[i].\n    No division allowed; O(n) time, O(1) extra space (output array not counted).\n\n    Two-pass prefix * suffix strategy:\n      Pass 1 (left->right): output[i] = product of all elements to the LEFT of i.\n      Pass 2 (right->left): multiply output[i] by the running suffix product\n                             (product of all elements to the RIGHT of i).\n\n    After both passes, output[i] = left_product[i] * right_product[i]\n    which equals the product of every element except nums[i].\n    \"\"\"\n    n = len(nums)\n    output = [1] * n\n\n    # Pass 1: output[i] = product of nums[0..i-1]\n    left = 1\n    for i in range(n):\n        output[i] = left\n        left *= nums[i]\n\n    # Pass 2: multiply by product of nums[i+1..n-1]\n    right = 1\n    for i in range(n - 1, -1, -1):\n        output[i] *= right\n        right *= nums[i]\n\n    return output\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import product_except_self\n\nclass TestProductExceptSelf(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_lc_example1(self):\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([1, 2, 3, 4]), [24, 12, 8, 6])\n\n    def test_lc_example2(self):\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([-1, 1, 0, -3, 3]), [0, 0, 9, 0, 0])\n\n    def test_two_elements(self):\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([3, 4]), [4, 3])\n\n    def test_single_zero(self):\n        # one zero: only the slot where zero lives gets nonzero\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([1, 0, 3, 4]), [0, 12, 0, 0])\n\n    def test_two_zeros(self):\n        # two zeros: all products are 0\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([0, 0, 2]), [0, 0, 0])\n\n    def test_negatives(self):\n        # (-2)*(-3)=6, (-1)*(-3)=3, (-1)*(-2)=2\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([-1, -2, -3]), [6, 3, 2])\n\n    def test_ones(self):\n        self.assertEqual(product_except_self([1, 1, 1, 1]), [1, 1, 1, 1])\n\n    def test_length_preserved(self):\n        nums = [2, 3, 4, 5]\n        self.assertEqual(len(product_except_self(nums)), len(nums))\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
