          "prompt": "Rebuild `eval_rpn(tokens)` (LC 150) from memory.\n\n- Push numbers; pop two for operators.\n- Order: pop `b` then `a`; compute `a op b`.\n- Division truncates toward zero: `int(a / b)`.",
          "solution": "def eval_rpn(tokens):\n    \"\"\"Recall: evaluate reverse polish notation from memory.\"\"\"\n    stack = []\n    for token in tokens:\n        if token in ('+', '-', '*', '/'):\n            b = stack.pop()\n            a = stack.pop()\n            if token == '+':\n                stack.append(a + b)\n            elif token == '-':\n                stack.append(a - b)\n            elif token == '*':\n                stack.append(a * b)\n            else:\n                stack.append(int(a / b))\n        else:\n            stack.append(int(token))\n    return stack[0]\n",
