          "prompt": "**Exercise 9 — Walls and Gates (LC 286)**\n\nWrite `walls_and_gates(rooms)` where `rooms` is a 2D grid: `-1` is a wall, `0` is a gate, and `2**31 - 1` (treat it as INF) is an empty room. Fill each empty room with the distance to its **nearest** gate, mutating `rooms` in place and returning it. Rooms that cannot reach any gate stay INF.\n\nUse **multi-source BFS**: seed the queue with every gate at once, then expand outward one ring at a time so the first time you reach a room is its shortest distance.",
          "solution": "from collections import deque\n\ndef walls_and_gates(rooms):\n    \"\"\"Fill each empty room with the distance to its nearest gate.\n    -1 = wall, 0 = gate, INF = empty room (we use 2**31 - 1 as INF).\n    Modifies rooms in place. Returns rooms.\n    Multi-source BFS seeded at all gates simultaneously.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not rooms or not rooms[0]:\n        return rooms\n\n    INF = 2**31 - 1\n    rows, cols = len(rooms), len(rooms[0])\n    queue = deque()\n    DIRS = [(0, 1), (1, 0), (-1, 0), (0, -1)]\n\n    # Seed all gate cells\n    for r in range(rows):\n        for c in range(cols):\n            if rooms[r][c] == 0:\n                queue.append((r, c))\n\n    while queue:\n        r, c = queue.popleft()\n        for dr, dc in DIRS:\n            nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc\n            if 0 <= nr < rows and 0 <= nc < cols and rooms[nr][nc] == INF:\n                rooms[nr][nc] = rooms[r][c] + 1\n                queue.append((nr, nc))\n\n    return rooms\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import walls_and_gates\n\nINF = 2**31 - 1\n\nclass TestWallsAndGates(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_example(self):\n        rooms = [\n            [INF,  -1,  0, INF],\n            [INF, INF, INF,  -1],\n            [INF,  -1, INF,  -1],\n            [  0,  -1, INF, INF]\n        ]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        # Gate at (0,2): fills nearby rooms\n        # Gate at (3,0): fills nearby rooms\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][2], 0)   # gate itself\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][3], 1)   # 1 step from (0,2)\n        self.assertEqual(result[3][0], 0)   # gate itself\n        self.assertEqual(result[2][0], 1)   # 1 step from (3,0)\n\n    def test_no_gates(self):\n        rooms = [[INF, INF], [INF, INF]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        # No gates means no updates\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[INF, INF], [INF, INF]])\n\n    def test_all_walls(self):\n        rooms = [[-1, -1], [-1, -1]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[-1, -1], [-1, -1]])\n\n    def test_gate_adjacent(self):\n        rooms = [[0, INF, INF]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[0, 1, 2]])\n\n    def test_two_gates(self):\n        rooms = [[0, INF, INF, INF, 0]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[0, 1, 2, 1, 0]])\n\n    def test_single_gate(self):\n        rooms = [[0]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[0]])\n\n    def test_empty_grid(self):\n        self.assertEqual(walls_and_gates([]), [])\n\n    def test_wall_blocks_path(self):\n        rooms = [[0, -1, INF]]\n        result = walls_and_gates(rooms)\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][2], INF)  # can't reach past wall\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
