          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Exercise 10 — Island Perimeter (LC 463)**\n\nWrite `island_perimeter(grid)` where `grid` is a list of lists of `0`s and `1`s containing exactly one island (no lakes). Return the perimeter of the island.\n\nTraverse the land cells (BFS) and, for each land cell, count how many of its 4 neighbours are water (`0`) or out of bounds — each such side adds 1 to the perimeter. Return `0` if there is no land.",
          "solution": "from collections import deque\n\ndef island_perimeter(grid):\n    \"\"\"Return the perimeter of the single island in the grid.\n    Uses BFS to traverse land cells and count exposed edges.\n    Each land cell contributes 1 to perimeter for each adjacent water cell or boundary.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not grid or not grid[0]:\n        return 0\n\n    rows, cols = len(grid), len(grid[0])\n    DIRS = [(0, 1), (1, 0), (-1, 0), (0, -1)]\n\n    # Find first land cell to start BFS\n    start = None\n    for r in range(rows):\n        for c in range(cols):\n            if grid[r][c] == 1:\n                start = (r, c)\n                break\n        if start:\n            break\n\n    if not start:\n        return 0\n\n    visited = {start}\n    queue = deque([start])\n    perimeter = 0\n\n    while queue:\n        r, c = queue.popleft()\n        for dr, dc in DIRS:\n            nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc\n            # Out of bounds or water = exposed edge\n            if nr < 0 or nr >= rows or nc < 0 or nc >= cols or grid[nr][nc] == 0:\n                perimeter += 1\n            elif (nr, nc) not in visited:\n                visited.add((nr, nc))\n                queue.append((nr, nc))\n\n    return perimeter\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import island_perimeter\n\nclass TestIslandPerimeter(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_all_water(self):\n        grid = [[0, 0], [0, 0]]\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 0)\n\n    def test_single_cell(self):\n        grid = [[1]]\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 4)\n\n    def test_two_cells_horizontal(self):\n        grid = [[1, 1]]\n        # Each cell has 3 exposed edges, shared edge removed: 2*4 - 2 = 6\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 6)\n\n    def test_two_cells_vertical(self):\n        grid = [[1], [1]]\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 6)\n\n    def test_square(self):\n        grid = [[1, 1], [1, 1]]\n        # 4 cells, 4*4 - 2*4(shared edges) = 16 - 8 = 8\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 8)\n\n    def test_l_shape(self):\n        grid = [\n            [0, 1, 0],\n            [1, 1, 0],\n            [0, 0, 0]\n        ]\n        # 3 cells, top-center + left-center + center\n        # perimeter: top-center has 3 exposed, shares 1 with center-center\n        # left-center has 3 exposed, shares 1 with center-center\n        # center-center: 2 neighbors -> 2 exposed sides\n        # total: 3+3+2 = 8\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 8)\n\n    def test_standard_example(self):\n        grid = [\n            [0, 1, 0, 0],\n            [1, 1, 1, 0],\n            [0, 1, 0, 0],\n            [1, 1, 0, 0]\n        ]\n        self.assertEqual(island_perimeter(grid), 16)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
