          "prompt": "**Exercise 11 — Flood Fill (LC 733)**\n\nWrite `flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color)` where `image` is a 2D list of ints. Starting at `(sr, sc)`, recolour every 4-directionally connected cell that shares the *original* colour of `(sr, sc)` with `color`, and return the modified image.\n\nEdge case: if `image[sr][sc]` already equals `color`, return `image` unchanged (don't loop forever — early-return).",
          "solution": "from collections import deque\n\ndef flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color):\n    \"\"\"Perform a flood fill on image starting at (sr, sc) with the given color.\n    Returns the modified image. LC 733 analog.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not image or not image[0]:\n        return image\n\n    rows, cols = len(image), len(image[0])\n    source_color = image[sr][sc]\n\n    # No-op if source already has target color\n    if source_color == color:\n        return image\n\n    DIRS = [(0, 1), (1, 0), (-1, 0), (0, -1)]\n    queue = deque([(sr, sc)])\n    image[sr][sc] = color\n\n    while queue:\n        r, c = queue.popleft()\n        for dr, dc in DIRS:\n            nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc\n            if (0 <= nr < rows and 0 <= nc < cols\n                    and image[nr][nc] == source_color):\n                image[nr][nc] = color\n                queue.append((nr, nc))\n\n    return image\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import flood_fill\n\nclass TestFloodFill(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic(self):\n        image = [[1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 1, 1, 2)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[2, 2, 2], [2, 2, 0], [2, 0, 1]])\n\n    def test_same_color_noop(self):\n        image = [[0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 0]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 0, 0)\n        # No change since color already matches\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 0]])\n\n    def test_single_cell(self):\n        result = flood_fill([[5]], 0, 0, 3)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[3]])\n\n    def test_corner_start(self):\n        image = [[1, 1], [1, 0]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 0, 9)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[9, 9], [9, 0]])\n\n    def test_diagonal_not_filled(self):\n        image = [[1, 0], [0, 1]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 0, 2)\n        # (1,1) is 1 but not 4-directionally connected\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[2, 0], [0, 1]])\n\n    def test_all_same_color(self):\n        image = [[3, 3], [3, 3]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 1, 0, 7)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[7, 7], [7, 7]])\n\n    def test_empty_grid(self):\n        self.assertEqual(flood_fill([], 0, 0, 1), [])\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
