          "prompt": "**Exercise 12 — Number of Connected Components (LC 323)**\n\nWrite `count_connected_components(n, edges)` where `n` is the number of nodes (labeled `0` to `n-1`) and `edges` is a list of `[u, v]` pairs. Return the number of connected components in the undirected graph.\n\nHints:\n- Build an adjacency list `dict` from edges.\n- Iterate all nodes 0..n-1; for each unvisited node, BFS to mark its entire component, then increment the counter.",
          "solution": "from collections import deque\n\ndef count_connected_components(n, edges):\n    \"\"\"Return the number of connected components in an undirected graph.\n    n: number of nodes (labeled 0 to n-1).\n    edges: list of [u, v] pairs.\n    Uses BFS. LC 323 analog.\n    \"\"\"\n    if n == 0:\n        return 0\n\n    # Build adjacency list\n    adj = {i: [] for i in range(n)}\n    for u, v in edges:\n        adj[u].append(v)\n        adj[v].append(u)\n\n    visited = set()\n    components = 0\n\n    for node in range(n):\n        if node not in visited:\n            # BFS to mark all nodes in this component\n            queue = deque([node])\n            visited.add(node)\n            while queue:\n                curr = queue.popleft()\n                for neighbor in adj[curr]:\n                    if neighbor not in visited:\n                        visited.add(neighbor)\n                        queue.append(neighbor)\n            components += 1\n\n    return components\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import count_connected_components\n\nclass TestCountComponents(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_zero_nodes(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(0, []), 0)\n\n    def test_single_node(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(1, []), 1)\n\n    def test_two_disconnected(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(2, []), 2)\n\n    def test_two_connected(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(2, [[0, 1]]), 1)\n\n    def test_fully_connected(self):\n        edges = [[0, 1], [1, 2], [2, 3]]\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(4, edges), 1)\n\n    def test_two_components(self):\n        # 0-1-2 and 3-4\n        edges = [[0, 1], [1, 2], [3, 4]]\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(5, edges), 2)\n\n    def test_all_isolated(self):\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(5, []), 5)\n\n    def test_three_components(self):\n        edges = [[0, 1], [2, 3]]\n        # 0-1, 2-3, 4 isolated = 3 components\n        self.assertEqual(count_connected_components(5, edges), 3)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
