          "type": "text",
          "value": "## The node class\n\nEvery linked-list solution in this module imports the same tiny class:\n\n```python\nclass ListNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.next = next\n```\n\nThat is the whole data structure. A linked list is just a chain of these objects: each node's `next` pointer points to the next node, and the last node's `next` is `None`.\n\nThe list `[1, 2, 3]` looks like this in memory:\n\n```\nListNode(1) -> ListNode(2) -> ListNode(3) -> None\n```\n\nYou hold a reference to the **head** node. Everything else is reachable by following `.next`."
