          "value": "## Two helper functions you will use everywhere\n\nIn tests and during interviews you constantly need to convert between plain Python lists and linked lists. Two small helpers do all the heavy lifting:\n\n```python\ndef list_to_nodes(values):\n    \"\"\"[1, 2, 3]  -->  ListNode(1) -> ListNode(2) -> ListNode(3) -> None\"\"\"\n    if not values:\n        return None\n    head = ListNode(values[0])\n    cur = head\n    for v in values[1:]:\n        cur.next = ListNode(v)\n        cur = cur.next\n    return head\n\ndef nodes_to_list(head):\n    \"\"\"ListNode(1) -> ...  -->  [1, 2, 3]\"\"\"\n    result = []\n    cur = head\n    while cur is not None:\n        result.append(cur.val)\n        cur = cur.next\n    return result\n```\n\nBoth run in O(n). You will import `ListNode`, `list_to_nodes`, and `nodes_to_list` from every exercise solution file throughout this module."
