          "prompt": "**Exercise 8 — Remove nth node from end (LC 19)**\n\nDefine `class ListNode`, the two helpers, and:\n\n`remove_nth_from_end(head, n)` — remove the nth node from the END (1-indexed) and return the new head. Solve it in **one pass** using two pointers separated by n+1 steps. Use a dummy head to handle head-removal cleanly.",
          "solution": "class ListNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.next = next\n\n\ndef list_to_nodes(values):\n    if not values:\n        return None\n    head = ListNode(values[0])\n    cur = head\n    for v in values[1:]:\n        cur.next = ListNode(v)\n        cur = cur.next\n    return head\n\n\ndef nodes_to_list(head):\n    result = []\n    cur = head\n    while cur is not None:\n        result.append(cur.val)\n        cur = cur.next\n    return result\n\n\ndef remove_nth_from_end(head, n):\n    \"\"\"LC 19 — Remove the nth node from the end in one pass.\n\n    Move fast n+1 steps ahead of slow (both start at dummy).\n    When fast is None, slow.next is the node to remove.\n    \"\"\"\n    dummy = ListNode(0)\n    dummy.next = head\n\n    slow = dummy\n    fast = dummy\n\n    for _ in range(n + 1):\n        fast = fast.next\n\n    while fast is not None:\n        slow = slow.next\n        fast = fast.next\n\n    slow.next = slow.next.next\n\n    return dummy.next\n",
