          "answer": 0,
          "explain": "If the list has [1,1,1,2] and we splice the second 1 out (cur.next = cur.next.next), cur.next now points to the third 1. We need to compare cur against this new cur.next again, so we DON'T advance cur yet. Moving cur only on a mismatch handles arbitrary-length runs of duplicates correctly."
