          "prompt": "**Exercise 4 — Range Count with bisect**\n\nWrite `count_in_range(nums, lo_val, hi_val)` where `nums` is a sorted list of integers (may have duplicates). Return the count of elements `x` satisfying `lo_val <= x <= hi_val`.\n\nUse `bisect.bisect_left` and `bisect.bisect_right`. One subtraction gives you the count. Import `bisect` inside the function.",
          "solution": "def count_in_range(nums, lo_val, hi_val):\n    \"\"\"Count elements in sorted nums that satisfy lo_val <= x <= hi_val.\n\n    Uses bisect_right(hi_val) - bisect_left(lo_val).\n    Demonstrates using bisect as a toolkit for range counting.\n    \"\"\"\n    import bisect\n    left = bisect.bisect_left(nums, lo_val)\n    right = bisect.bisect_right(nums, hi_val)\n    return right - left\n",
