          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Exercise 10 — First Bad Version (LC 278 analog)**\n\nWrite `first_bad_version(n, is_bad)` where versions are numbered 1 to `n`. `is_bad(k)` is a callable that returns `True` if version `k` is bad (all versions >= the first bad are bad). Find and return the number of the first bad version.\n\nRequirements:\n- `while lo < hi` with `lo = 1`, `hi = n`\n- When `is_bad(mid)` is True: `hi = mid` (mid could be the first bad)\n- When `is_bad(mid)` is False: `lo = mid + 1` (first bad is after mid)\n- Return `lo`",
          "solution": "def first_bad_version(n, is_bad):\n    \"\"\"LC 278 analog - first bad version.\n\n    Given versions 1..n, find the first bad one.\n    is_bad(k) returns True if version k is bad (all versions >= first_bad are bad).\n    Classic binary search on answer with a boolean predicate.\n    \"\"\"\n    lo, hi = 1, n\n    while lo < hi:\n        mid = (lo + hi) // 2\n        if is_bad(mid):\n            hi = mid        # mid or something earlier is the first bad\n        else:\n            lo = mid + 1    # first bad is strictly after mid\n    return lo\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import first_bad_version\n\n\nclass TestFirstBadVersion(unittest.TestCase):\n\n    def _make_is_bad(self, first_bad):\n        return lambda v: v >= first_bad\n\n    def test_basic(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(5, self._make_is_bad(4)), 4)\n\n    def test_first_is_bad(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(10, self._make_is_bad(1)), 1)\n\n    def test_last_is_bad(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(10, self._make_is_bad(10)), 10)\n\n    def test_single_version_bad(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(1, self._make_is_bad(1)), 1)\n\n    def test_middle(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(100, self._make_is_bad(50)), 50)\n\n    def test_two_versions_second_bad(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(2, self._make_is_bad(2)), 2)\n\n    def test_two_versions_first_bad(self):\n        self.assertEqual(first_bad_version(2, self._make_is_bad(1)), 1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    unittest.main()\n"
