          "prompt": "**Exercise 7 — Path sum (LC112)**\n\nDefine `TreeNode` and implement `has_path_sum(root, target_sum)` that returns `True` if any root-to-leaf path sums to `target_sum`.\n\nRemember:\n- A **leaf** has both `left` and `right` equal to `None`.\n- Return `False` immediately for an empty root.\n- Subtract `root.val` before recursing so you don't need to carry a running sum.",
          "solution": "class TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.left = left\n        self.right = right\n\n\ndef has_path_sum(root, target_sum):\n    \"\"\"Check whether tree has a root-to-leaf path summing to target — LC112.\n\n    A leaf is a node with no children.\n    Recursively subtract val from target; at a leaf, check if remainder == 0.\n    \"\"\"\n    if root is None:\n        return False\n    # At a leaf: is this the last value we needed?\n    if root.left is None and root.right is None:\n        return root.val == target_sum\n    # Otherwise recurse with reduced target\n    remaining = target_sum - root.val\n    return has_path_sum(root.left, remaining) or has_path_sum(root.right, remaining)\n",
