          "solution": "class TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.left = left\n        self.right = right\n\n\ndef is_valid_bst(root):\n    \"\"\"Validate that a binary tree satisfies the BST invariant — LC98.\n\n    Naive approach (check left < root < right at each node) is WRONG for\n    subtrees deeper than one level.  The correct approach threads a valid\n    range [lo, hi] down the recursion.\n\n    At every node:\n      - root.val must be strictly inside (lo, hi).\n      - Going left tightens the upper bound to root.val.\n      - Going right tightens the lower bound to root.val.\n    \"\"\"\n    def validate(node, lo, hi):\n        if node is None:\n            return True\n        if not (lo < node.val < hi):\n            return False\n        return (validate(node.left, lo, node.val) and\n                validate(node.right, node.val, hi))\n\n    return validate(root, float('-inf'), float('inf'))\n",
