          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Exercise 6 — Flood Fill (LC 733)**\n\nWrite `flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color)` that performs a flood fill starting at cell `(sr, sc)` of a 2D pixel grid, replacing the original color at that cell and all 4-directionally connected cells of the same original color with the new `color`.\n\n- If `image[sr][sc] == color` already, return `image` unchanged (prevents infinite recursion).\n- Modify and return `image` in place.\n- Use DFS recursively, checking bounds and color match before recursing.\n\n```python\ndef flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color):\n    rows, cols = len(image), len(image[0])\n    original = image[sr][sc]\n    if original == color:\n        return image\n    def dfs(r, c):\n        # your code\n        pass\n    dfs(sr, sc)\n    return image\n```",
          "solution": "def flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color):\n    \"\"\"Flood fill starting at (sr, sc) with new color (LC 733).\n\n    Args:\n        image: 2D list of ints representing pixel colors\n        sr: starting row\n        sc: starting column\n        color: new fill color\n\n    Returns:\n        modified image (in-place)\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = len(image), len(image[0])\n    original = image[sr][sc]\n\n    # If already the target color, nothing to do\n    if original == color:\n        return image\n\n    def dfs(r, c):\n        if r < 0 or r >= rows or c < 0 or c >= cols:\n            return\n        if image[r][c] != original:\n            return\n        image[r][c] = color\n        dfs(r + 1, c)\n        dfs(r - 1, c)\n        dfs(r, c + 1)\n        dfs(r, c - 1)\n\n    dfs(sr, sc)\n    return image\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import flood_fill\n\n\nclass TestFloodFill(unittest.TestCase):\n\n    def test_basic(self):\n        image = [[1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 1, 1, 2)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[2, 2, 2], [2, 2, 0], [2, 0, 1]])\n\n    def test_same_color_no_change(self):\n        image = [[0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 0]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 0, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 0]])\n\n    def test_single_pixel(self):\n        result = flood_fill([[5]], 0, 0, 9)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[9]])\n\n    def test_surrounded_pixel(self):\n        image = [[1, 0, 1], [0, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 1, 1, 3)\n        self.assertEqual(result[1][1], 3)\n        # Neighbors are 0, should not change\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][0], 1)\n\n    def test_entire_grid_same_color(self):\n        image = [[1, 1], [1, 1]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 0, 7)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[7, 7], [7, 7]])\n\n    def test_corner_start(self):\n        image = [[1, 2, 2], [1, 2, 0], [1, 0, 0]]\n        result = flood_fill(image, 0, 1, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][1], 5)\n        self.assertEqual(result[0][2], 5)\n        self.assertEqual(result[1][1], 5)\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
