          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "applied",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Exercise 12 — Number of Provinces (LC 547)**\n\nWrite `num_provinces(is_connected)` where `is_connected` is an `n x n` matrix with `is_connected[i][j] == 1` meaning cities `i` and `j` are directly connected. Return the number of provinces (connected components).\n\n- Treat the matrix as an implicit adjacency list: neighbors of city `i` are all `j` where `is_connected[i][j] == 1`.\n- Use DFS with a visited set.\n- `is_connected[i][i] == 1` always (self-loop); handle it naturally (already visited).\n\n```python\ndef num_provinces(is_connected):\n    n = len(is_connected)\n    visited = set()\n    count = 0\n    def dfs(city):\n        visited.add(city)\n        for neighbor in range(n):\n            if is_connected[city][neighbor] == 1 and neighbor not in visited:\n                dfs(neighbor)\n    # your code here\n    pass\n```",
          "solution": "from collections import defaultdict\n\n\ndef num_provinces(is_connected):\n    \"\"\"Count number of provinces (connected components) in a city graph (LC 547).\n\n    is_connected[i][j] == 1 means cities i and j are directly connected.\n    Uses DFS over the adjacency matrix interpreted as an adjacency list.\n\n    Args:\n        is_connected: n x n matrix where is_connected[i][j] in {0,1}\n\n    Returns:\n        integer count of provinces\n    \"\"\"\n    n = len(is_connected)\n    visited = set()\n    count = 0\n\n    def dfs(city):\n        visited.add(city)\n        for neighbor in range(n):\n            if is_connected[city][neighbor] == 1 and neighbor not in visited:\n                dfs(neighbor)\n\n    for city in range(n):\n        if city not in visited:\n            dfs(city)\n            count += 1\n\n    return count\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import num_provinces\n\n\nclass TestNumProvinces(unittest.TestCase):\n\n    def test_all_separate(self):\n        mat = [[1, 0, 0], [0, 1, 0], [0, 0, 1]]\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces(mat), 3)\n\n    def test_all_connected(self):\n        mat = [[1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 1]]\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces(mat), 1)\n\n    def test_two_provinces(self):\n        mat = [[1, 1, 0], [1, 1, 0], [0, 0, 1]]\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces(mat), 2)\n\n    def test_single_city(self):\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces([[1]]), 1)\n\n    def test_chain(self):\n        mat = [[1, 1, 0, 0],\n               [1, 1, 1, 0],\n               [0, 1, 1, 1],\n               [0, 0, 1, 1]]\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces(mat), 1)\n\n    def test_two_pairs(self):\n        mat = [[1, 1, 0, 0],\n               [1, 1, 0, 0],\n               [0, 0, 1, 1],\n               [0, 0, 1, 1]]\n        self.assertEqual(num_provinces(mat), 2)\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
