          "value": "## Clone Graph (LC 133)\n\nCloning a graph with cycles is a classic BFS + hashmap problem. The trick: maintain a `{original_node: cloned_node}` dictionary as you traverse. When you encounter a node already in the map, return the existing clone instead of creating a duplicate.\n\n```python\nclones = {}  # old -> new\n\ndef get_clone(n):\n    if n not in clones:\n        clones[n] = Node(n.val)\n    return clones[n]\n```\n\nBFS visits each original node once. For each original node, wire up the clone's `.neighbors` list to the clones of its neighbors."
