          "value": "# LC547 — read from adjacency matrix, same DSU logic.\n\ndef find_circle_num(isConnected):\n    n = len(isConnected)\n    dsu = DSU(n)  # reusing the class above\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(i + 1, n):   # upper triangle: j > i\n            if isConnected[i][j] == 1:\n                dsu.union(i, j)\n    return dsu.components\n\n# LC547 examples\nmat1 = [[1,1,0],[1,1,0],[0,0,1]]\nmat2 = [[1,0,0],[0,1,0],[0,0,1]]\nprint(find_circle_num(mat1))  # 2\nprint(find_circle_num(mat2))  # 3"
