          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "cumulative",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "LC210 — Course Schedule II. Full implementation from scratch.\n\n`find_order_capstone(numCourses, prerequisites)` where `prerequisites[i] = [a, b]` means take course b before course a.\n\nReturn a valid order to take all courses, or `[]` if impossible.\n\nWrite the complete Kahn's algorithm without referring to any previous solution:\n1. Allocate adj and in_degree.\n2. For each [a, b]: add edge b->a, increment in_degree[a].\n3. Seed queue with zero-in-degree courses.\n4. BFS loop: dequeue, record, decrement neighbors, enqueue if zero.\n5. Return order if complete, [] if not.",
          "solution": "from collections import deque\n\ndef find_order_capstone(numCourses, prerequisites):\n    adj = [[] for _ in range(numCourses)]\n    in_degree = [0] * numCourses\n\n    for a, b in prerequisites:\n        adj[b].append(a)   # b must precede a\n        in_degree[a] += 1\n\n    queue = deque()\n    for i in range(numCourses):\n        if in_degree[i] == 0:\n            queue.append(i)\n\n    order = []\n    while queue:\n        course = queue.popleft()\n        order.append(course)\n        for next_course in adj[course]:\n            in_degree[next_course] -= 1\n            if in_degree[next_course] == 0:\n                queue.append(next_course)\n\n    return order if len(order) == numCourses else []\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import find_order_capstone\n\ndef is_valid_course_order(order, numCourses, prerequisites):\n    if len(order) != numCourses:\n        return False\n    if set(order) != set(range(numCourses)):\n        return False\n    pos = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(order)}\n    for a, b in prerequisites:\n        if pos[b] >= pos[a]:\n            return False\n    return True\n\nclass TestFindOrderCapstone(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_single_course_no_prereqs(self):\n        result = find_order_capstone(1, [])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [0])\n\n    def test_lc210_example1(self):\n        result = find_order_capstone(2, [[1, 0]])\n        self.assertTrue(is_valid_course_order(result, 2, [[1, 0]]))\n\n    def test_lc210_example2(self):\n        prereqs = [[1,0],[2,0],[3,1],[3,2]]\n        result = find_order_capstone(4, prereqs)\n        self.assertTrue(is_valid_course_order(result, 4, prereqs))\n\n    def test_cycle_impossible(self):\n        result = find_order_capstone(2, [[0, 1], [1, 0]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [])\n\n    def test_three_course_cycle(self):\n        result = find_order_capstone(3, [[1,0],[2,1],[0,2]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [])\n\n    def test_no_prerequisites_large(self):\n        result = find_order_capstone(6, [])\n        self.assertEqual(len(result), 6)\n        self.assertEqual(set(result), set(range(6)))\n\n    def test_linear_chain(self):\n        prereqs = [[1,0],[2,1],[3,2],[4,3]]\n        result = find_order_capstone(5, prereqs)\n        self.assertTrue(is_valid_course_order(result, 5, prereqs))\n\n    def test_multiple_valid_roots(self):\n        prereqs = [[2,0],[2,1]]\n        result = find_order_capstone(3, prereqs)\n        self.assertTrue(is_valid_course_order(result, 3, prereqs))\n\n    def test_complex_dag(self):\n        prereqs = [[4,0],[4,1],[3,1],[3,2]]\n        result = find_order_capstone(5, prereqs)\n        self.assertTrue(is_valid_course_order(result, 5, prereqs))\n\n    def test_cycle_with_attached_dag(self):\n        prereqs = [[1,0],[2,1],[4,3],[3,4]]\n        result = find_order_capstone(5, prereqs)\n        self.assertEqual(result, [])\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
