          "solution": "def subsets(nums):\n    \"\"\"\n    LC 78 - Subsets.\n    Return all subsets (the power set) of nums. No duplicates in input.\n    Uses the choose -> recurse -> un-choose backtracking template.\n    \"\"\"\n    result = []\n\n    def backtrack(start, current):\n        # Record the current partial selection as a subset\n        result.append(list(current))\n\n        for i in range(start, len(nums)):\n            # CHOOSE: add nums[i] to the current selection\n            current.append(nums[i])\n            # RECURSE: only look at elements after i (avoid re-using)\n            backtrack(i + 1, current)\n            # UN-CHOOSE: remove nums[i], restoring state for the next iteration\n            current.pop()\n\n    backtrack(0, [])\n    return result\n",
