          "solution": "def permute(nums):\n    \"\"\"\n    LC 46 - Permutations.\n    Return all permutations of distinct integers.\n    Uses a 'used' boolean array to track which elements are in the current path.\n    \"\"\"\n    result = []\n    used = [False] * len(nums)\n\n    def backtrack(current):\n        # Base case: a complete permutation\n        if len(current) == len(nums):\n            result.append(list(current))\n            return\n\n        for i in range(len(nums)):\n            if used[i]:\n                continue\n            # CHOOSE: mark nums[i] as used and add to path\n            used[i] = True\n            current.append(nums[i])\n            # RECURSE\n            backtrack(current)\n            # UN-CHOOSE: restore state\n            current.pop()\n            used[i] = False\n\n    backtrack([])\n    return result\n",
