          "prompt": "Implement `climb_stairs(n)` (LC 70).\n\n- You can climb 1 or 2 steps. Return the number of distinct ways to reach the top.\n- Recurrence: `ways(i) = ways(i-1) + ways(i-2)`\n- Base cases: `n=0` or `n=1` → return 1.\n- Use the space-optimized rolling-pair approach (two variables, no array).",
          "solution": "def climb_stairs(n):\n    # LC 70 - Climbing Stairs.\n    # State: dp[i] = number of distinct ways to reach step i.\n    # Recurrence: dp[i] = dp[i-1] + dp[i-2]  (take 1 or 2 steps)\n    # Base: dp[0]=1, dp[1]=1\n    if n <= 1:\n        return 1\n    prev2, prev1 = 1, 1\n    for i in range(2, n + 1):\n        prev2, prev1 = prev1, prev2 + prev1\n    return prev1\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import climb_stairs\n\nclass TestClimbStairs(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_base_n0(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(0), 1)   # empty staircase: 1 way (do nothing)\n\n    def test_base_n1(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(1), 1)\n\n    def test_n2(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(2), 2)   # [1+1] or [2]\n\n    def test_n3(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(3), 3)   # [1+1+1],[1+2],[2+1]\n\n    def test_n4(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(4), 5)\n\n    def test_n10(self):\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(10), 89)\n\n    def test_large(self):\n        # just checking it runs fast and is correct\n        self.assertEqual(climb_stairs(45), 1836311903)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
