          "answer": 1,
          "explain": "Coins outer means: for each coin denomination, you decide how many of that coin to use before moving on. This naturally groups by combination (unordered multiset). If you put amounts outer and coins inner, you'd count ordered sequences — 1+2 and 2+1 would each be counted."
