          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "applied",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Interval scheduling by earliest finish (greedy).** Write `max_nonoverlapping(intervals)` where `intervals` is a list of `(start, end)` tuples (half-open: an interval ending at `t` does not conflict with one starting at `t`). Return the maximum number of mutually non-overlapping intervals you can select. The greedy choice: sort by **end** time and walk left to right, taking an interval whenever its start is at or after the end of the last interval you took. `max_nonoverlapping([(1, 3), (2, 4), (3, 5)])` returns `2`; `max_nonoverlapping([])` returns `0`; `max_nonoverlapping([(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)])` returns `3`; `max_nonoverlapping([(1, 10), (2, 9), (3, 8)])` returns `1`.",
          "solution": "def max_nonoverlapping(intervals):\n    if not intervals:\n        return 0\n    # Greedy: always keep the interval that finishes earliest, because\n    # finishing earlier leaves the most room for the rest.\n    intervals = sorted(intervals, key=lambda pair: pair[1])\n    count = 0\n    current_end = None\n    for start, end in intervals:\n        if current_end is None or start >= current_end:\n            count += 1\n            current_end = end\n    return count\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import max_nonoverlapping\n\n\nclass ExerciseTests(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic(self):\n        # (1,3) and (3,5) are compatible; (2,4) overlaps both -> keep 2.\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([(1, 3), (2, 4), (3, 5)]), 2)\n\n    def test_empty(self):\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([]), 0)\n\n    def test_single(self):\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([(0, 1)]), 1)\n\n    def test_all_disjoint(self):\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)]), 3)\n\n    def test_all_overlap(self):\n        # All share a common point -> only one can be chosen.\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([(1, 10), (2, 9), (3, 8)]), 1)\n\n    def test_touching_endpoints_compatible(self):\n        # end == next start is allowed (half-open intervals).\n        self.assertEqual(max_nonoverlapping([(1, 2), (2, 3), (3, 4)]), 3)\n\n    def test_unsorted_input_earliest_finish_wins(self):\n        # Given out of order; sorting by finish time yields 3 picks.\n        self.assertEqual(\n            max_nonoverlapping([(8, 9), (0, 3), (3, 5), (1, 2)]), 3\n        )\n"
