          "kind": "cumulative",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Greedy change-making — combine the greedy-choice idea with sorting (m6) and a dict (m3).** Write `make_change(amount, coins)` where `coins` is a list of canonical denominations (like US coins `[1, 5, 10, 25]`). Return a **dict** mapping each used coin to the number of times it is used, choosing coins greedily: repeatedly take as many of the largest coin that fits as possible, then move to the next-largest. Sort `coins` descending yourself; only include coins actually used (count > 0). `make_change(41, [1, 5, 10, 25])` returns `{25: 1, 10: 1, 5: 1, 1: 1}`; `make_change(0, [1, 5, 10, 25])` returns `{}`; `make_change(30, [1, 5, 10, 25])` returns `{25: 1, 5: 1}`; `make_change(36, [10, 1, 25, 5])` returns `{25: 1, 10: 1, 1: 1}`. (This is the lesson's Problem A — greedy is correct for canonical denominations.)",
          "solution": "def make_change(amount, coins):\n    # Greedy: repeatedly take the largest coin that fits. Correct for\n    # canonical (e.g. US) denominations. Sort descending so the biggest\n    # coin is tried first.\n    counts = {}\n    for coin in sorted(coins, reverse=True):\n        if amount <= 0:\n            break\n        n = amount // coin\n        if n > 0:\n            counts[coin] = n\n            amount -= coin * n\n    return counts\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import make_change\n\n\nclass ExerciseTests(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic_41(self):\n        # 41 = 25 + 10 + 5 + 1\n        self.assertEqual(\n            make_change(41, [1, 5, 10, 25]),\n            {25: 1, 10: 1, 5: 1, 1: 1},\n        )\n\n    def test_zero_amount(self):\n        self.assertEqual(make_change(0, [1, 5, 10, 25]), {})\n\n    def test_single_denomination(self):\n        self.assertEqual(make_change(7, [1]), {1: 7})\n\n    def test_only_uses_needed_coins(self):\n        # 30 = 25 + 5; no dimes, no pennies appear in the dict.\n        self.assertEqual(make_change(30, [1, 5, 10, 25]), {25: 1, 5: 1})\n\n    def test_multiple_of_one_coin(self):\n        # 75 = 25 * 3\n        self.assertEqual(make_change(75, [1, 5, 10, 25]), {25: 3})\n\n    def test_unsorted_input(self):\n        # Coins given out of order; the function sorts descending itself.\n        self.assertEqual(\n            make_change(36, [10, 1, 25, 5]),\n            {25: 1, 10: 1, 1: 1},\n        )\n\n    def test_exact_largest(self):\n        self.assertEqual(make_change(25, [1, 5, 10, 25]), {25: 1})\n"
