          "kind": "cumulative",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "**Greedy interval selection grouped by owner — combine greedy with sorting (m6) and a dict tally (m3).** Write `schedule_by_owner(activities)` where each activity is a `(start, end, owner)` tuple (half-open intervals). Greedily select the maximum set of non-overlapping activities by earliest finish time (sort by `end`, take an activity when its start is at or after the last taken activity's end). Return a **dict** mapping each owner to the count of that owner's **selected** activities (owners with zero selected activities do not appear). `schedule_by_owner([(3, 5, \"a\"), (1, 2, \"a\"), (2, 4, \"b\")])` returns `{\"a\": 1, \"b\": 1}`; `schedule_by_owner([])` returns `{}`; `schedule_by_owner([(1, 2, \"a\"), (2, 3, \"a\"), (3, 4, \"a\")])` returns `{\"a\": 3}`; `schedule_by_owner([(1, 3, \"b\"), (2, 9, \"a\"), (2, 8, \"c\")])` returns `{\"b\": 1}`.",
          "solution": "def schedule_by_owner(activities):\n    # Greedy interval scheduling (sort by finish time, pick if it starts at or\n    # after the last pick's end) combined with a dict that tallies how many\n    # selected activities belong to each owner.\n    selected_counts = {}\n    current_end = None\n    for start, end, owner in sorted(activities, key=lambda a: a[1]):\n        if current_end is None or start >= current_end:\n            current_end = end\n            selected_counts[owner] = selected_counts.get(owner, 0) + 1\n    return selected_counts\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import schedule_by_owner\n\n\nclass ExerciseTests(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic(self):\n        # Sorted by finish: (1,2,'a'),(2,4,'b'),(3,5,'a') -> pick (1,2,'a')\n        # then (2,4,'b'); (3,5,'a') overlaps -> dropped.\n        activities = [(3, 5, \"a\"), (1, 2, \"a\"), (2, 4, \"b\")]\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner(activities), {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 1})\n\n    def test_empty(self):\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner([]), {})\n\n    def test_single(self):\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner([(0, 1, \"x\")]), {\"x\": 1})\n\n    def test_same_owner_multiple(self):\n        # Three disjoint intervals all owned by 'a'.\n        activities = [(1, 2, \"a\"), (2, 3, \"a\"), (3, 4, \"a\")]\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner(activities), {\"a\": 3})\n\n    def test_all_overlap_one_winner(self):\n        # All overlap; earliest finish (1,3,'b') wins, only 'b' counted.\n        activities = [(1, 3, \"b\"), (2, 9, \"a\"), (2, 8, \"c\")]\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner(activities), {\"b\": 1})\n\n    def test_touching_endpoints(self):\n        activities = [(1, 2, \"a\"), (2, 3, \"b\"), (3, 4, \"a\")]\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner(activities), {\"a\": 2, \"b\": 1})\n\n    def test_unsorted_input(self):\n        activities = [(5, 6, \"z\"), (0, 3, \"y\"), (3, 5, \"y\"), (1, 2, \"y\")]\n        # sort by end: (1,2,y)e2,(0,3,y)e3,(3,5,y)e5,(5,6,z)e6\n        # pick (1,2,y); (0,3,y) start0<2 skip; (3,5,y) pick; (5,6,z) pick\n        self.assertEqual(schedule_by_owner(activities), {\"y\": 2, \"z\": 1})\n"
