          "type": "exercise",
          "kind": "recall",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "Implement `assign_cookies(g, s)` — LC 455.\n\n- `g`: list of children's greediness factors (integers)\n- `s`: list of cookie sizes (integers)\n- Return the maximum number of children you can satisfy.\n\nGreedy rule: sort both lists, then use two pointers. Advance the cookie pointer every iteration. Advance the child pointer only when the current cookie satisfies the current child (`s[cookie] >= g[child]`). Return the child count at the end.",
          "solution": "def assign_cookies(g, s):\n    # Greedy invariant: satisfy least-greedy child first with smallest sufficient cookie.\n    g.sort()\n    s.sort()\n    child = 0\n    cookie = 0\n    while child < len(g) and cookie < len(s):\n        if s[cookie] >= g[child]:\n            child += 1  # this cookie satisfies this child\n        cookie += 1     # try next cookie either way\n    return child\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import assign_cookies\n\nclass TestAssignCookies(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_example1(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([1, 2, 3], [1, 1]), 1)\n\n    def test_example2(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([1, 2], [1, 2, 3]), 2)\n\n    def test_no_cookies(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([1, 2, 3], []), 0)\n\n    def test_no_children(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([], [1, 2, 3]), 0)\n\n    def test_all_satisfied(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 1]), 3)\n\n    def test_none_satisfied(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([5, 10], [1, 2, 3]), 0)\n\n    def test_single_match(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([3], [3]), 1)\n\n    def test_single_no_match(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([5], [3]), 0)\n\n    def test_one_big_cookie(self):\n        self.assertEqual(assign_cookies([1, 2], [10]), 1)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
