          "kind": "applied",
          "mode": "sync",
          "prompt": "Re-implement `can_complete_circuit(gas, cost)` — LC 134 — and make sure you handle all edge cases correctly.\n\nSame O(n) greedy: single pass tracking `total`, `tank`, `start`. Return `start` if `total >= 0`, else `-1`.\n\nEdge cases you must handle:\n- Single station: return 0 if `gas[0] >= cost[0]`, else -1.\n- All-equal gas and cost: valid, return 0.\n- Total deficit by any amount: return -1.\n- Start forced to last index by dead zone covering 0..n-2.",
          "solution": "def can_complete_circuit(gas, cost):\n    total = 0\n    tank = 0\n    start = 0\n    for i in range(len(gas)):\n        diff = gas[i] - cost[i]\n        total += diff\n        tank += diff\n        if tank < 0:\n            start = i + 1\n            tank = 0\n    return start if total >= 0 else -1\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import can_complete_circuit\n\nclass TestGasStationApplied(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_lc_example1(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([1,2,3,4,5], [3,4,5,1,2]), 3)\n\n    def test_lc_example2(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([2,3,4], [3,4,3]), -1)\n\n    def test_single_possible(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([10], [3]), 0)\n\n    def test_single_impossible(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([1], [5]), -1)\n\n    def test_start_at_last_index(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([1,1,10], [5,5,1]), 2)\n\n    def test_uniform_break_even(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([3,3,3], [3,3,3]), 0)\n\n    def test_impossible_by_one(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([1,2,3], [2,3,3]), -1)\n\n    def test_large_first_station(self):\n        self.assertEqual(can_complete_circuit([5,1,1], [1,4,2]), 0)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n"
