          "prompt": "**LC 378 — Kth Smallest Element in a Sorted Matrix**\n\nImplement `kth_smallest(matrix, k)`. Each row and column is sorted ascending.\n\n1. Push `(matrix[row][0], row, 0)` for each row (up to min(n, k) rows — no need beyond that).\n2. Loop k times: pop `(val, row, col)`; if `col+1 < len(matrix[row])`, push the next element in that row.\n3. After k pops, return `val`.\n\nEdge cases: 1x1 matrix, k=1 (global min), k=n² (global max), duplicate values.",
          "solution": "import heapq\n\n\ndef kth_smallest(matrix, k):\n    n = len(matrix)\n    heap = []\n    # Seed with first element of each row (smallest in each row)\n    for row in range(min(n, k)):\n        heapq.heappush(heap, (matrix[row][0], row, 0))\n\n    val = 0\n    for _ in range(k):\n        val, row, col = heapq.heappop(heap)\n        if col + 1 < len(matrix[row]):\n            heapq.heappush(heap, (matrix[row][col + 1], row, col + 1))\n    return val\n",
