          "type": "code",
          "run": true,
          "value": "# The sort-sweep skeleton in its purest form.\n# LC252 Meeting Rooms I: can one person attend all meetings?\n\ndef can_attend_all(intervals):\n    # Step 1: sort by start time.\n    intervals.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\n\n    # Step 2: sweep — check each adjacent pair.\n    for i in range(1, len(intervals)):\n        # Strict <: touching endpoints are NOT a conflict.\n        if intervals[i][0] < intervals[i - 1][1]:\n            return False\n    return True\n\nprint(can_attend_all([[0, 5], [10, 15], [20, 25]]))   # True\nprint(can_attend_all([[0, 10], [5, 15]]))              # False — 5 < 10\nprint(can_attend_all([[0, 5], [5, 10]]))               # True — touching only\nprint(can_attend_all([]))                              # True — no meetings"
