          "prompt": "LC56 Merge Intervals.\n\nGiven a list of intervals (possibly unsorted, possibly overlapping), merge all overlapping intervals and return the minimal list of non-overlapping intervals.\n\n**Key mechanics:**\n- Sort by start time.\n- Overlap condition: `cur[0] <= prev[1]` (use `<=` so touching endpoints merge).\n- On overlap: `prev[1] = max(prev[1], cur[1])` — don't shrink if current is contained.\n- Work by mutating the last element of your `merged` list in place.\n\nImplement `merge(intervals: list[list[int]]) -> list[list[int]]`.",
          "solution": "def merge(intervals):\n    \"\"\"\n    LC56 Merge Intervals.\n\n    Sort by start, then sweep: if the current interval overlaps the last\n    merged interval (cur.start <= merged[-1].end), extend the end.\n    Otherwise push a new merged interval.\n\n    Overlap condition: cur[0] <= prev_end\n    (<=  because [0,5],[5,10] share endpoint => merge into [0,10])\n\n    Time O(n log n), Space O(n) for output.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not intervals:\n        return []\n\n    # Sort by start time.\n    intervals.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\n\n    merged = [intervals[0][:]]  # copy the first interval\n\n    for cur in intervals[1:]:\n        prev = merged[-1]\n        if cur[0] <= prev[1]:\n            # Overlap — extend the end of the last merged interval.\n            prev[1] = max(prev[1], cur[1])\n        else:\n            # No overlap — start a new merged interval.\n            merged.append(cur[:])\n\n    return merged\n",
          "tests": "import unittest\nfrom solution import merge\n\n\nclass TestMerge(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_basic(self):\n        result = merge([[1, 3], [2, 6], [8, 10], [15, 18]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 6], [8, 10], [15, 18]])\n\n    def test_touching(self):\n        # [1,4] and [4,5] share endpoint — should merge\n        result = merge([[1, 4], [4, 5]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 5]])\n\n    def test_empty(self):\n        self.assertEqual(merge([]), [])\n\n    def test_single(self):\n        self.assertEqual(merge([[2, 4]]), [[2, 4]])\n\n    def test_all_merge(self):\n        result = merge([[1, 10], [2, 5], [3, 8]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 10]])\n\n    def test_none_merge(self):\n        result = merge([[1, 2], [3, 4], [5, 6]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 2], [3, 4], [5, 6]])\n\n    def test_unsorted_input(self):\n        result = merge([[15, 18], [1, 3], [2, 6], [8, 10]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 6], [8, 10], [15, 18]])\n\n    def test_contained_interval(self):\n        # [1,10] fully contains [2,5]\n        result = merge([[1, 10], [2, 5]])\n        self.assertEqual(result, [[1, 10]])\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    unittest.main()\n"
