          "solution": "import copy\n\ndef flood_fill(image, sr, sc, color):\n    \"\"\"\n    LC 733 - Flood Fill.\n    Paint the connected region containing (sr, sc) with `color`.\n    Uses DFS with a direction-vector loop.\n    Mutates a deep copy and returns it (Pyodide-safe).\n    \"\"\"\n    image = copy.deepcopy(image)\n    original = image[sr][sc]\n    if original == color:\n        return image  # nothing to do; avoids infinite recursion\n\n    rows, cols = len(image), len(image[0])\n    DIRS = [(0, 1), (1, 0), (0, -1), (-1, 0)]  # 4-directional\n\n    def dfs(r, c):\n        if r < 0 or r >= rows or c < 0 or c >= cols:\n            return\n        if image[r][c] != original:\n            return\n        image[r][c] = color  # mark before recursing to avoid revisiting\n        for dr, dc in DIRS:\n            dfs(r + dr, c + dc)\n\n    dfs(sr, sc)\n    return image\n",
