          "prompt": "Implement `is_palindrome(s: str) -> bool` (LC 125).\n\nRules:\n- Only alphanumeric characters count; ignore everything else.\n- Comparison is case-insensitive.\n- Empty string → `True`.\n\nUse a two-pointer approach on the filtered+lowercased characters. Do NOT use `s == s[::-1]` — the point is to practice the pointer pattern.",
          "solution": "def is_palindrome(s):\n    \"\"\"LC 125 - Valid Palindrome.\n    Filter to alphanumeric, lowercase, then two-pointer from both ends.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Step 1: clean the string to only alnum chars, lowercased\n    cleaned = [c.lower() for c in s if c.isalnum()]\n\n    # Step 2: two-pointer squeeze from both ends\n    left, right = 0, len(cleaned) - 1\n    while left < right:\n        if cleaned[left] != cleaned[right]:\n            return False\n        left += 1\n        right -= 1\n    return True\n",
