          "prompt": "This is **LeetCode 399, \"Evaluate Division,\"** as a black-box walk. An injected `neighbors(unit)` returns a LIST of `(next_unit, rate)` edges leaving `unit`, where `rate = unit / next_unit`. Write `convert(src, dst, neighbors)` that returns the conversion factor `src / dst` by DFS, multiplying rates along the path (start the accumulator at `1.0`). Normalize both unit names (strip + lowercase). Guard cycles with a seen-set. Return `-1.0` if either unit is unknown (src has no edges and isn't dst) or no path connects them. A known unit converted to itself is `1.0`. Only CALL `neighbors`; never read its data.",
          "solution": "def convert(src, dst, neighbors):\n    # LeetCode 399 \"Evaluate Division\" as a black-box walk.\n    # `neighbors(unit)` is an injected source: it returns a list of\n    # (next_unit, rate) edges leaving `unit`, where rate = unit / next_unit.\n    # We DFS, multiplying rates along the path, and return the product\n    # src/dst, or -1.0 if either unit is unknown or no path connects them.\n    src = src.strip().lower()\n    dst = dst.strip().lower()\n\n    # An unknown unit (no outgoing edges and never seen as a target) cannot\n    # be converted. We discover \"known\" lazily: if src has no edges AND is\n    # not the dst, it is unknown.\n    start_edges = neighbors(src)\n    if not start_edges and src != dst:\n        return -1.0\n\n    seen = set()\n\n    def dfs(unit, acc):\n        if unit == dst:\n            return acc            # reached the target; acc holds src/unit so far\n        seen.add(unit)\n        for nxt, rate in neighbors(unit):\n            if nxt in seen:\n                continue          # cycle guard\n            found = dfs(nxt, acc * rate)\n            if found != -1.0:\n                return found      # propagate the first successful product\n        return -1.0               # this branch dead-ended\n\n    # Same unit converts to itself at 1.0, but only if the unit is known.\n    if src == dst:\n        return 1.0\n    return dfs(src, 1.0)\n",
